l></div><div class="doc-footer"><span>Independent candidate work product for USAA · github.com/russelldudek/USAA</span><span class="page-number">Interview Brief · 2</span></div></section><section class="paper"><div class="doc-header"><div><div class="doc-name">Russell Dudek</div><div class="doc-role">Process Excellence, Automation &amp; Operating Transformation Leader</div></div><div class="doc-contact"><img alt="USAA" class="doc-logo" src="assets/brand/usaa-logo-official.png"/><strong>Russell Dudek</strong><br/>Pittsburgh, PA · Planning relocation to Tampa/St. Petersburg<br/><a href="tel:+14122878640">412.287.8640</a> · <a href="mailto:russelldudek@gmail.com">russelldudek@gmail.com</a><br/><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/russelldudek">linkedin.com/in/russelldudek</a><br/><a href="https://russelldudek.github.io/USAA/">russelldudek.github.io/USAA/</a></div></div><h1 class="brief-title">Proof Map</h1><div class="doc-section"><h2>Vape-Jet - current operating transformation</h2><p><strong>Evidence:</strong> AI-first transformation across production, purchasing, quality, customer success, support, engineering issue flow, Odoo, Jira, HubSpot, Slack, telemetry, and AI-assisted workflows.</p><p><strong>Transfer:</strong> workflow integration, signal-to-action mechanisms, standard work, team development, and adoption inside live operations.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>DudeWorth - automation opportunity and governance</h2><p><strong>Evidence:</strong> frameworks for value, feasibility, data readiness, governance, adoption burden, reuse, and time-to-value; agentic workflow patterns with human judgment, escalation, decision records, evaluation, and governance rails.</p><p><strong>Transfer:</strong> portfolio selection, business cases, human authority, evidence standards, and AI/automation governance.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Amazon - high-volume operating mechanisms</h2><p><strong>Evidence:</strong> 24/7 Prime operation supporting approximately five million second-day orders annually; leadership routines, labor planning, throughput visibility, escalation, standard work, Lean, and Gemba.</p><p><strong>Transfer:</strong> fact-based prioritization, leader coaching, cadence, flow visibility, and continuous improvement at scale.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Compunetics - high-reliability process control</h2><p><strong>Evidence:</strong> engineering, manufacturing, quality, customer delivery, high-reliability programs, quality systems, root cause, measures, and controls.</p><p><strong>Transfer:</strong> process engineering, risk-conscious execution, technical translation, and disciplined quality systems.</p></div><div class="doc-callout"><h2>Strongest objection</h2><p>No claim of direct USAA RPA-platform or financial-services COE ownership. The case is adjacent operating discipline plus explicit platform/regulatory learning. A separate qualification gap remains: the record lists Six Sigma Certification but does not yet verify Green Belt level or three named projects.</p></div><div class="doc-footer"><span>Independent candidate work product for USAA · github.com/russelldudek/USAA</span><span class="page-number">Interview Brief · 3</span></div></section><section class="paper"><div class="doc-header"><div><div class="doc-name">Russell Dudek</div><div class="doc-role">Process Excellence, Automation &amp; Operating Transformation Leader</div></div><div class="doc-contact"><img alt="USAA" class="doc-logo" src="assets/brand/usaa-logo-official.png"/><strong>Russell Dudek</strong><br/>Pittsburgh, PA · Planning relocation to Tampa/St. Petersburg<br/><a href="tel:+14122878640">412.287.8640</a> · <a href="mailto:russelldudek@gmail.com">russelldudek@gmail.com</a><br/><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/russelldudek">linkedin.com/in/russelldudek</a><br/><a href="https://russelldudek.github.io/USAA/">russelldudek.github.io/USAA/</a></div></div><h1 class="brief-title">120-Day Entry and Executive Questions</h1><div class="plan-grid"><div class="plan-card"><b>Days 1-30</b><h3>Read the system</h3><ul><li>Portfolio, platforms, governance, risk, process intelligence.</li><li>Stakeholder decision rights and team capability.</li><li>Value baselines and evidence gaps.</li></ul></div><div class="plan-card"><b>Days 31-60</b><h3>Align decisions</h3><ul><li>Common intake and selection logic.</li><li>Work/assurance paired review.</li><li>Escalation, authority, monitoring standards.</li></ul></div><div class="plan-card"><b>Days 61-90</b><h3>Prove mechanism</h3><ul><li>Apply to bounded portfolio cases.</li><li>Close assurance and measurement gaps.</li><li>Coach Process Engineers in live reviews.</li></ul></div><div class="plan-card"><b>Days 91-120</b><h3>Scale learning</h3><ul><li>Reusable standards and platform guidance.</li><li>Capability development and operating cadence.</li><li>Quarterly value/control portfolio review.</li></ul></div></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Executive questions</h2><ol><li>Where does the automation portfolio most need to change: selection, delivery, controls, value realization, or adoption?</li><li>Which member-friction outcomes are shared across BPM, Member Value, and business lines?</li><li>What decisions belong to the COE, process owners, risk partners, and platform teams?</li><li>How mature are process mining, task mining, and continuous monitoring?</li><li>Which control-evidence gaps most often delay scale?</li><li>What must the Process Engineers become better at over the next year?</li><li>How does projected automation value become validated realized value?</li><li>What visible change at twelve months defines success?</li></ol></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Source boundary</h2><p>Company observations use the USAA 2025 Annual Report, official newsroom mission materials, the supplied job posting, and public reporting on regulatory context. Internal-state statements are hypotheses for discovery.</p></div><div class="doc-footer"><span>Independent candid